.TH "DOMTokenList.value" "JS" "April 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
DOMTokenList.value \- DOMTokenList: value property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]value\f[B]\f[R] property of the \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R]
interface is a stringifier that returns the value of the list serialized
as a string, or clears and sets the list to the given value.
.SH VALUE
A string representing the serialized content of the list.
Each item is separated by a space.
.SH EXAMPLES
In the following example we retrieve the list of classes set on a
\f[CR]<span>\f[R] element as a \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] using
\f[CR]Element.classList\f[R], then write the value of the list to the
\f[CR]<span>\f[R]\[cq]s \f[CR]Node.textContent\f[R].
.PP
First, the HTML:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]span\f[R] class=\[dq]a b c\[dq]></\f[B]span\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
Now the JavaScript:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] span = document.querySelector(\[dq]span\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] classes = span.classList;
span.textContent = classes.value;
.EE
.PP
